{'contentformat': 'text/x-wiki', 'contentmodel': 'wikitext', '*': '{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Electric}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/GO|species=Luxio}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Electric|prevnum=403|prev=Shinx|nextnum=405|next=Luxray|round=none}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Disambig|species=Luxio}}\n|}\n{{Pokémon Infobox\n|name=Luxio\n|jname=ルクシオ\n|jtranslit=Rukushio\n|tmname=Luxio\n|ndex=404\n|sdex=018\n|abrow=050\n|obrow=124\n|opbrow=044\n|typebox=1\n|type1=Electric\n|category=Spark\n|height-ftin=2\'11"\n|height-m=0.9\n|weight-lbs=67.2\n|weight-kg=30.5\n|abilityn=d\n|ability1=Rivalry\n|ability2=Intimidate\n|abilityd=Guts\n|egggroupn=1\n|egggroup1=Field\n|eggcycles=20\n|evtotal=2\n|evat=2\n|expyield=127\n|oldexp=117\n|lv100exp=1,059,860\n|gendercode=127\n|color=Blue\n|catchrate=120\n|body=08\n|pokefordex=luxio\n|generation=4\n|friendship=100\n}}\n\'\'\'Luxio\'\'\' ([[List of Japanese Pokémon names|Japanese]]: \'\'\'ルクシオ\'\'\' \'\'Luxio\'\') is an {{type|Electric}} {{OBP|Pokémon|species}} introduced in [[Generation IV]].\n\nIt [[Evolution|evolves]] from {{p|Shinx}} starting at [[level]] 15 and evolves into {{p|Luxray}} starting at level 30.\n\n==Biology==\nLuxio is a feline, quadruped Pokémon resembling a young lynx or lion. Blue and black fur covers most of its body. Its ears, face, hind paws, and front half of its body are blue, while its hindquarters are black. Additionally, Luxio has a tufty black mane surrounding its face. The mane is longer on the male Luxio, while the fur on the hind paws extends to ankles on the female. The insides of its rounded ears are yellow, as are its eyes. There are two yellow rings around each front leg and a yellow, four-point star on the tip of its tail. Luxio is able to communicate with others of its kind using {{wp|Electroreception|electrical pulses from its claws}}. Luxio lives in small groups, and is able to generate powerful electricity by gathering the group\'s tails together.\n\n==In the anime==\n[[File:Clemont Luxio.png|thumb|left|250px|Luxio in the {{pkmn|anime}}]]\n===Major appearances===\n====[[Clemont\'s Luxio]]====\nIn \'\'[[XY048|A Campus Reunion!]]\'\', {{an|Clemont}} {{pkmn2|caught}} a Luxio, which, prior to the episode, evolved from a Shinx that he befriended. In \'\'[[XY062|The Future Is Now, Thanks to Determination!]]\'\', Luxio evolved into a Luxray.\n\n====Other====\nLuxio\xa0debuted in \'\'[[M10|The Rise of Darkrai]]\'\', where it was among the Pokémon residing in a garden in [[Alamos Town]]. Luxio seemed to be shy, as it hesitated before it ran to {{Ash}} and {{ashfr}}\' Pokémon. It later participated in a near-skirmish between two groups of Pokémon, caused by a misunderstanding. Afterwards, it was a bystander during the battle between {{mov|Dialga}} and {{mov|Palkia}}.\n\nLuxio made its main series debut in \'\'[[DP109|Leading a Stray!]]\'\', where it helped a {{p|Wailmer}} that was trapped in the sewers. As a result, the Wailmer made it back into the ocean safely and evolved into a {{p|Wailord}} before rejoining its pod.\n\n===Minor appearances===\nA Luxio made a brief cameo in the opening sequence of \'\'[[M11|Giratina and the Sky Warrior]]\'\'.\n\nA Luxio appeared in \'\'[[DP149|Sticking With Who You Know!]]\'\'.\n\nA Luxio appeared in \'\'[[DP160|A Marathon Rivalry!]]\'\', under the ownership of a competitor in the [[Pokéathlon]] held in [[Camellia Town]].\n\n===Pokédex entries===\n{{Animedexheader|Sinnoh}}\n{{Animedexbody|DP109|Luxio|Ash\'s Pokédex|Luxio, the Spark Pokémon. By touching friends with its front paws, Luxio is able to communicate through the {{m|Spark|sparks}} it emits.}}\n{{Animedexfooter/Pokémon|\'\'Diamond & Pearl\'\'|Sinnoh}}\n{{Animedexheader|Kalos}}\n{{Animedexbody|XY048|Luxio|Ash\'s Pokédex|Luxio, the Spark Pokémon, and the evolved form of Shinx. Luxio\'s sharp claws conduct electricity, and the slightest scratch can knock out an opponent.}}\n{{Animedexfooter/Pokémon|\'\'XY\'\'|Kalos}}\n\n==In the manga==\n[[File:Rayler Luxio.png|thumb|200px|Luxio in [[Pokémon Adventures]]]]\n===In the Pokémon Adventures manga===\n{{main|Rayler}}\n{{adv|Platinum}} was attacked by a pack of {{pkmn2|wild}} {{p|Shinx}} and Luxio in \'\'[[PS340|Extreme Luxio]]\'\'. One of them, due to his broken claws, was unable to communicate with his group and was shunned by them. In an attempt to regain his group\'s favor, he battled with {{adv|Diamond}}\'s Pokémon. {{adv|Pearl}} eventually managed to get his comrades\' trust and befriended the Luxio. Later, he evolved into a Luxray and joined Pearl\'s team after being named Rayler.\n\nMultiple Luxio appeared in \'\'[[PS349|Passing by Probopass and Maneuvering around Magnezone]]\'\'.\n\nTwo Luxio appeared in \'\'[[PS389|Cautious Clefairy]]\'\'.\n\nIn \'\'[[PS435|The Final Dimensional Duel V]]\'\', a Luxio appeared on [[Fullmoon Island]] in {{FB|Tower Tycoon|Palmer}}\'s flashback.\n\n===In the Pokémon Diamond and Pearl Adventure! manga===\n{{main|Hareta\'s Luxio}}\n[[Hareta]]\'s {{p|Shinx}} evolved into Luxio after defeating [[B-2]] on [[Iron Island]] in \'\'[[DPA10|Serious Training on Iron Island!!]]\'\'. His {{pkmn|Trainer}} attempted to use him against [[Cyrus]]\'s {{p|Gyarados}} at [[Lake Valor]], but he was instead ambushed by [[Saturn]]\'s {{p|Rhyperior}}, who had been [[revive]]d after being [[Fainting|knocked out]]. Later, he evolved into {{p|Luxray}} during Hareta\'s {{si|Pokémon League}} {{pkmn|battle}} with [[Koya]].\n\n===In the Pokémon + Nobunaga\'s Ambition ~ Ranse\'s Color Picture Scroll ~ manga===\nA Luxio appeared in \'\'[[PNA2|The Green Scroll: Kenshin\'s Adventure]]\'\', under the ownership of [[Ginchiyo]].\n\n==In the TCG==\n{{main|Luxio (TCG)}}\n\n==Game data==\n===NPC appearances===\n* [[Pokémon Mystery Dungeon: Explorers of Time and Explorers of Darkness]]: [[Amp Plains tribes|Luxray and the Luxio Tribe]] are the bosses of [[Amp Plains]]. In [[Pokémon Mystery Dungeon: Explorers of Sky]], they are replaced by {{p|Manectric}} and the {{p|Electrike}} tribe.\n\n===Pokédex entries==